
# LingOrm × Dior AW2026 Caption Generator

Luxury-minimal caption generator designed for coordinated global support of  
**LingOrm as Dior Brand Ambassadors** during Paris Fashion Week AW2026.

Created by **the_wanderer16**

---

## 🌍 Live Site

https://lingorm-caption-generator.pages.dev

---

# ✨ Purpose

This tool was built to:

- Standardize support posts across X, Threads, Instagram, and Facebook
- Ensure correct hashtag usage for global monitoring (Lefty / EMV tracking)
- Maintain consistent mention structure for Dior and LingOrm
- Reduce caption duplication across multiple users
- Make coordinated posting easier on both desktop and mobile

This is a static tool.  
No data is collected. No captions are stored remotely.

---

# 🖤 Core Principle

All posts should:
- Maintain alignment with Dior’s image
- Support global data tracking via consistent hashtag usage

---

# 🧭 Platform Modes

The generator supports:

### 1️⃣ X (Posts)
- Enforced 280 character limit
- Optimized for stacked hashtags
- CTA automatically disabled

---

### 2️⃣ Threads (Posts)
- Similar to X
- Allows CTA
- Uses primary hashtag block

---

### 3️⃣ Threads (Replies / Quotes) ⚠ CRITICAL MODE

This mode enforces the official coordination guideline:

Required in every reply/quote:

- `#LingOrmDiorAW26`
- `#pfw`
- `@Dior`
- `@linglingkwong`
- `@orm.kornnaphat`

If these are missing from the Threads Reply block, generation will stop.

This ensures:
- Proper Paris Fashion Week tagging
- Accurate Lefty tracking
- Full brand visibility

---

### 4️⃣ Instagram (Posts)
- Multi-line stacked hashtag formatting
- CTA enabled
- Supports @dior tagging

---

### 5️⃣ Facebook (Posts)
- Optimized stacked formatting
- CTA enabled

---

# 🏷 Hashtag Blocks (Editable)

The “Hashtag blocks” section is always visible.

You may edit:

- X post block
- Instagram post block
- Facebook post block
- Threads Post / Reply / Quote block

⚠ Editing the Threads block must still include required tags.

---

# 🧠 Caption Engine Logic

Each caption is generated using:

Subject  
Fashion descriptor  
Anchor (PFW / DiorAW26 context)  
Authority statement (as Dior Brand Ambassadors)  
Optional ending line  

Randomized structure templates:
- Sentence + separate ending
- Combined single paragraph
- Ending first, then statement

Occasionally injects full names:
> Lingling Kwong and Orm Kornnaphat

This helps improve monitoring coverage and SOV tracking.

---

# 🔁 Duplicate Detection

Two levels of duplicate control:

### 1️⃣ Within Current Batch
If the same caption appears twice in one generation:
- It will be marked **DUPLICATE**

---

### 2️⃣ Seen Before (This Device Only)
Previously generated captions are stored locally in your browser.
If a new caption matches an older one:
- It will be marked **SEEN**

You may clear history anytime using:
> Clear duplicate history (this device)

No server storage is used.

---

# 🗂 BANK System

You may paste your own BANK using tab-separated format.

Required 5 columns:
Subject | Fashion | Anchor | Authority | |Ending

Format:
- Tab separated columns
- One row per line
- Optional header row allowed

Example:
LingOrm | embody modern Dior elegance | at Paris Fashion Week for DiorAW26 | as Dior Brand Ambassadors | A defining Paris moment.

The generator requires **at least 3 valid rows**.

**‼️If you are unsure on what to do, just don't update anything in the BANK (LINGORM) section‼️**

